[
India
] (= 

Eucrate indica


n. sp.

)

Diagnosis.
Third anterolateral tooth absent or reduced as slight elevation, carapace with relatively long posterolateral borders (
Figs. 2C
; 
4A–C
). P5 propodus slender (
Fig. 2C
). Varying number of large, irregular red-brown spots across carapace, with smaller, anterior spots or dots (
Fig. 2C
).

Colour pattern.
There is some variation in the pattern of spots on the carapace (
Figs. 2C
; 
4A, B
). The dorsal surface of the carapace invariably has a varying number of large, often irregular red-brown spots across in addition to smaller spots or dots anterior to the large spots. The anterior spots vary from medium-size spots that decrease in size anteriorly to many spots of evenly small size.
